        "## Technical Implementation\n",
        "\n",
        "The NGS Figure Generator is built as a modular web-based application that integrates data processing, visualization, and user interaction.\n",
        "\n",
        "### Frontend\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Framework:** React (with component libraries such as shadcn/ui)\n",
        "- Provides a user-friendly interface for:\n",
        "  - uploading sequencing data (CSV/TXT)\n",
        "  - selecting visualization parameters\n",
        "  - customizing figure outputs in real time\n",
        "\n",
        "### Backend\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Language:** Python\n",
        "- **Frameworks:** Flask or FastAPI\n",
        "- Handles:\n",
        "  - data ingestion and preprocessing\n",
        "  - computation of analytical outputs\n",
        "  - generation of visualizations\n",
        "\n",
        "### Data Processing & Visualization\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Data handling:** pandas  \n",
        "- **Statistical and ML methods:** scikit-learn (e.g., PCA)  \n",
        "- **Visualization libraries:**\n",
        "  - Matplotlib / Seaborn → static, publication-ready figures  \n",
        "  - Plotly → interactive visualizations  \n",
        "\n",
        "### Supported Visualizations\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Volcano & MA plots:** Matplotlib  \n",
        "- **Heatmaps:** Seaborn / Matplotlib  \n",
        "- **PCA:** scikit-learn (computation) + Plotly (interactive rendering)  \n",
        "\n",
        "### File Handling\n",
        "\n",
        "- Supports structured input formats (CSV, TXT)\n",
        "- Designed for integration with standard bioinformatics outputs\n",
        "\n",
        "### Deployment & Reproducibility\n",
        "\n",
        "- Containerized using Docker for consistent environments  \n",
        "- Deployable as a local server-based application  \n",
